# DS Component from Figma

Use this rule when building a new Design System component from a Figma spec.

## Project structure

```
packages/
  design-tokens/          → @ds-12/design-tokens
    src/
      tokens.generated.css  ← Style Dictionary output, do NOT edit
      tokens.web.css        ← web-specific layer, exported as tokens.css
      tokens.theme.css      ← generated @theme inline bridge for Tailwind v4
    scripts/
      generate-theme.mjs    ← regenerates tokens.theme.css
  ui/                     → @ds-12/ui
    src/
      tailwind.css          ← Tailwind v4 entry + migrated component @utility CSS
      style.css             ← legacy component CSS (not yet migrated)
      components/           ← DS components (lowercase folder names)
      lib/
        utils.ts            ← cn() helper (clsx + tailwind-merge)
  utils/                  → @ds-12/utils
apps/
  storybook/              ← component stories + Vite aliases for local dev
```

## Package names & imports

| Package | Import examples |
|---|---|
| `@ds-12/design-tokens` | `@ds-12/design-tokens/tokens.css`, `@ds-12/design-tokens/theme.css` |
| `@ds-12/ui` | `@ds-12/ui/button`, `@ds-12/ui/tailwind.css`, `@ds-12/ui/style.css` |

Apps using `@ds-12/ui` must configure Tailwind v4 and import `@ds-12/ui/tailwind.css` in global CSS. Storybook does this in `.storybook/styles.css` with `@tailwindcss/vite` in `.storybook/main.ts`.

**Migrated components** (Badge, Avatar, Typography) — CSS is imported in `packages/ui/src/tailwind.css`, **not** side-effect-imported from `index.tsx`:

```css
/* packages/ui/src/tailwind.css */
@import "./components/badge/badge.css";
```

**Legacy components** (Button, Chip, Input, …) — still use `@layer components` / `ds-*` classes and are bundled via `packages/ui/src/style.css`. Migrate them to the `@utility` pattern when touching them.

## Step 1 — Setup tokens.web.css

Update `packages/design-tokens/src/tokens.web.css` (create if missing):

```css
@import "./tokens.generated.css";

:root {
  /* --- Web platform extensions --- */
  /* Focus ring, cursor, border-style, transition */

  /* --- Component tokens: [component] --- */
  /* Map to tokens.generated.css; add TODOs for unmapped Figma values */
}
```

Rules:
- Only add web-specific tokens or tokens missing from `tokens.generated.css`
- Do NOT duplicate or override values already in `tokens.generated.css`
- Prefer aliasing generated/semantic tokens: `--badge-radius: var(--radius-xsmall);`
- If a design token is wrong or missing, add a TODO and flag it as a Design System issue — do not silently fix it here

```css
/* TODO: needs token — current value: 20px */
```

### Token resolution (colors)

Resolve color values in this order:

1. **Repo tokens** — search `packages/design-tokens/src/tokens.generated.css` and `tokens.web.css` for a matching `--token-name`.
2. **Figma Variables** — if no repo token matches (or the generated name differs), call Figma MCP `get_variable_defs` with the component `fileKey` and `nodeId`. Variables return canonical names and resolved values, e.g. `color/semantic/canvas-moderate` → `#f7f8f8`.
3. **Map variable → CSS custom property** — convert the Figma path to the repo naming convention: slash segments become hyphens, prefixed with `--`.

   | Figma variable | Repo CSS custom property |
   |---|---|
   | `color/semantic/canvas-moderate` | `--color-semantic-canvas-moderate` |
   | `color/semantic/text-brand-bold` | `--color-semantic-text-brand-bold` |
   | `color/semantic/border-information-bold` | `--color-semantic-border-information-bold` |

4. **Re-check repo tokens** — after mapping, grep `tokens.generated.css` again for that `--color-*` name. If it exists, use `var(--color-semantic-…)`.
5. **Alias in `tokens.web.css`** — if the Figma variable resolves to a value that only exists under a different generated token (e.g. Figma `border-information-bold` → repo `--color-blue-500`), alias the component token to the generated one and leave a TODO noting the naming gap.
6. **Last resort** — if the variable is not in Figma and not in repo tokens, add a TODO with the Figma variable path and resolved hex/rgba value. Do not hardcode colors in component CSS.

For non-color tokens (spacing, radius, typography), prefer repo tokens first; use `get_variable_defs` only when the Figma spec references a variable name that does not appear in `tokens.generated.css`.

After editing `tokens.generated.css` or `tokens.web.css`, regenerate the Tailwind bridge:

```bash
vp run @ds-12/design-tokens#generate:theme
```

## Step 2 — Fetch component from Figma

Use Figma MCP (`get_design_context`) to fetch the target component by node ID.

Extract:
- Variants and visual differences between them
- Spacing, sizing, typography values
- Border, radius, shadow, color per variant and state (hover, focus, disabled)

Cross-reference each raw value against `tokens.generated.css` (see **Token resolution** above for colors):
- Match found → use `var(--token-name)`
- Color with no repo match → `get_variable_defs` → map to `--color-*` → alias in `tokens.web.css` or TODO
- No match after both sources → TODO comment with Figma variable path and resolved value in `tokens.web.css`

## Step 3 — Build the component

Create files under `packages/ui/src/components/[name]/` (lowercase, e.g. `button`, `badge`):

```
[name]/
  index.tsx
  [name].css          ← Tailwind v4 @utility blocks (required for visual components)
```

### Stack

- **Base UI** (`@base-ui/react`) — interactive primitives (e.g. `Button`, `useRender`, `Avatar`)
- **CVA** (`class-variance-authority`) — variant class names wired to `@utility` presets
- **Tailwind v4 `@utility`** — component styles as named utilities in `[name].css`
- **Design tokens** — all visual values via `var(--token)` from `@ds-12/design-tokens/tokens.css`
- **`cn()`** — from `../../lib/utils.ts` when merging optional `className` props

Reference implementations: `badge/`, `avatar/`, `typography/`.

### Architecture — `@utility` + CVA `compoundVariants`

Follow this split consistently:

1. **`[name].css`** — `@utility` blocks for styles that are **identical across a group** or form a **named preset**:
   - Base layout (`@utility badge`, `@utility avatar`)
   - Child parts (`badge-icon`, `avatar-initials`)
   - Size presets (`badge-preset-size-sm`, `avatar-preset-size-md`)
   - Variant combination presets (`badge-neutral-subtle`, `avatar-circle`, `typography-preset-heading-h1-bold`)

2. **`index.tsx`** — CVA maps props to those utility class names via `compoundVariants`. **Do not** put arbitrary Tailwind values like `bg-[var(--token)]` in CVA when a named `@utility` exists.

3. **Props that change per variant** (colour, size, weight, spacing) → `compoundVariants` referencing real token-backed `@utility` presets. Only generate combinations that exist in the design tokens — do not invent pairings.

4. **Props/types** — use a discriminated union when different variants support different sub-props (see `Typography`). If that adds too much complexity, use optional props + JSDoc + dev-mode `console.warn` for invalid combinations.

5. **DOM attributes** — `data-slot="[name]"` and `data-variant="{variant}"` on the root element. This is the primary debug/test hook, not BEM class names.

6. **Defaults** — set `defaultVariants` in CVA to the most common visual state; check actual usage in `apps/*` before assuming.

### What NOT to do

- Do **not** use `@apply` to bundle utilities into one BEM-style class — conflicts with `tailwind-merge` composability.
- Do **not** use arbitrary Tailwind values in CVA (`bg-[var(--…)]`) when a named `@utility` preset is the right abstraction.
- Do **not** guess at design tokens — if the source CSS / Figma spec has no token for a combination, stop and flag it rather than fabricating one.
- Do **not** remove `data-slot` / `data-variant` attributes.
- Do **not** side-effect-import `[name].css` from `index.tsx` for migrated components — register it in `tailwind.css` instead.

### Naming conventions

| Layer | Pattern | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Folder | lowercase | `packages/ui/src/components/badge/` |
| Base utility | `[name]` | `@utility badge` |
| Child part | `[name]-[part]` | `@utility badge-icon` |
| Size preset | `[name]-preset-size-[size]` | `@utility badge-preset-size-sm` |
| Variant preset | `[name]-[axis]-[value]` or `[name]-[combo]` | `@utility badge-neutral-subtle`, `@utility avatar-circle` |
| Typography preset | `typography-preset-[variant]-[combo]` | `@utility typography-preset-paragraph-default` |
| CVA base class | `[name]` | `cva("badge", …)` |

### Component tokens (`tokens.web.css`)

Define component-scoped aliases in `tokens.web.css`:

```css
/* --- Component tokens: badge --- */
--badge-radius: var(--radius-xsmall);
--badge-sm-gap: var(--spacing-xxsmall);
--badge-neutral-subtle-fill: var(--color-semantic-neutral-subtle);
--badge-neutral-subtle-label-fill: var(--color-semantic-text-neutral-bold);
/* TODO: needs token — current value: 20px */
--badge-lg-icon-size: 20px;
```

Consume them in `[name].css` `@utility` presets — not as intermediate `--badge-fill` indirection on modifier classes:

```css
@utility badge-neutral-subtle {
  background-color: var(--badge-neutral-subtle-fill);
  color: var(--badge-neutral-subtle-label-fill);
}
```

### CSS file structure (`[name].css`)

```css
/* Base layout — identical across all variants */
@utility badge {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  border-radius: var(--badge-radius);
}

/* Child parts */
@utility badge-icon {
  display: inline-flex;
  color: inherit;
}

/* Size presets */
@utility badge-preset-size-sm {
  gap: var(--badge-sm-gap);
  padding: var(--badge-sm-padding);
  font-size: var(--badge-sm-label-font-size);
}

/* Variant combination presets */
@utility badge-neutral-subtle {
  background-color: var(--badge-neutral-subtle-fill);
  color: var(--badge-neutral-subtle-label-fill);
}
```

Register the file in `packages/ui/src/tailwind.css`:

```css
@import "./components/badge/badge.css";
```

### CVA pattern

Use empty strings on variant axes; apply real classes via `compoundVariants`:

```ts
import { cva } from "class-variance-authority";
import { cn } from "../../lib/utils.ts";

const badgeVariants = cva("badge", {
  variants: {
    size: { sm: "", lg: "" },
    emphasis: { subtle: "", bold: "" },
    variant: { neutral: "", negative: "", attention: "", positive: "", information: "" },
  },
  compoundVariants: [
    { size: "sm", class: "badge-preset-size-sm" },
    { size: "lg", class: "badge-preset-size-lg" },
    { emphasis: "subtle", variant: "neutral", class: "badge-neutral-subtle" },
    { emphasis: "bold", variant: "neutral", class: "badge-neutral-bold" },
    // …only combinations that exist in tokens
  ],
  defaultVariants: {
    size: "lg",
    emphasis: "subtle",
    variant: "neutral",
  },
});
```

Root element:

```tsx
<span
  className={cn(badgeVariants({ size, emphasis, variant, className }))}
  data-slot="badge"
  data-variant={resolvedVariant}
  {...props}
>
```

Separate CVA configs for child parts when they have their own size axis (e.g. `badgeIconVariants`, `avatarIconVariants`).

### Icons

Use the shared `Icon` component with `@material-symbols/font-400`:

```tsx
import { Icon } from "../icon/index.tsx";

<Icon name="check_circle" variant="filled" />
```

`Icon` reads size from `BadgeIconSizeContext` when nested inside `Badge`.

### Rules

- No hardcoded visual values — use a token or leave a TODO comment
- Variants and states must map to the Figma spec
- Do not add visual opinions outside of what Figma specifies
- Export the component from `packages/ui/src/index.ts`

## Step 4 — Storybook

Add `apps/storybook/src/components/[name]/[name].stories.tsx`:

```ts
import type { Meta, StoryObj } from "@storybook/react-vite";
import { Badge, type BadgeVariant } from "@ds-12/ui/badge";
```

Storybook resolves `@ds-12/ui/*` imports via the `@ds-12/ui` alias in `apps/storybook/vite.config.ts` (maps to `packages/ui/src/components`).

Add a subpath export in `packages/ui/package.json`:

```json
"./badge": "./src/components/badge/index.tsx"
```

### Story patterns

- Use a typed `ComponentStory` wrapper when Controls need a wider args surface than the component's discriminated union (see `TypographyStory`, `BadgeStory`, `AvatarStory`).
- Use `argTypes` with conditional `if:` to hide invalid prop combinations (see Typography `size`/`weight` controls).
- Assert `data-slot` and `data-variant` in `play` functions — not CSS class names.
- Extract large showcase matrices into `[name]-story-fixtures.tsx`.
- Follow `tags: ["autodocs"]`, variant/size controls, and a `TypesAndVariants` / `AllVariants` showcase story (`tags: ["!manifest"]`).

## Step 5 — Validate

```bash
cd packages/ui && vp check
cd apps/storybook && pnpm run build-storybook
cd apps/storybook && pnpm exec playwright test   # visual snapshots
```

Run snapshot tests after style changes to confirm no visual regression.

## Output checklist

- [ ] `packages/design-tokens/src/tokens.web.css` updated with component token aliases
- [ ] `packages/ui/src/components/[name]/index.tsx` created with CVA + `data-slot` / `data-variant`
- [ ] `packages/ui/src/components/[name]/[name].css` created with `@utility` blocks (base, parts, presets)
- [ ] `packages/ui/src/tailwind.css` imports `[name].css`
- [ ] `packages/ui/src/index.ts` exports the component and types
- [ ] `packages/ui/package.json` has a `./[name]` subpath export
- [ ] `apps/storybook/src/components/[name]/[name].stories.tsx` created
- [ ] Color tokens resolved via repo tokens or Figma Variables (`get_variable_defs`) before falling back to TODOs
- [ ] All unmapped values have `/* TODO: needs token — current value: … */` comments (include Figma variable path when known)
- [ ] Playwright snapshots pass (`pnpm exec playwright test` in `apps/storybook`)
- [ ] List of TODOs that require Design System decisions (token missing, token wrong, design ambiguous, Figma/repo naming mismatch)
